    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for beings who inhabit the spiritual or otherworldly realms, or who inhabit the physical world but have powers and abilities of the supernatural.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000006371/Dictionary of Comparative Religion (1970)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Algemene term voor wezens die een spirituele of bovenaardse wereld bewonen, of die de fysieke wereld bewonen maar bovennatuurlijke krachten of vaardigheden bezitten.
</Note_Text>
